<PageLayout>
    <h1>&#47;&#42;&#42;</h1>
    <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10 mt-10">
        <span class="text-4xl">&#42;</span>
        <i
            >Mediocrity is a disease, an insidious force that dulls the edges of
            our creativity and ambition. It's the easy path, the one littered
            with half-hearted efforts and "good enough" solutions. We see it
            everywhere - in the bloated software, the uninspired designs, the
            lackluster games. This isn't just about missing the mark; it's about
            a mindset that accepts the bare minimum and calls it a day.</i
        >
    </p>
    <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10 mt-10">
        <span class="text-4xl">&#42;</span>
        <i
            >But why do we tolerate it? Is it fear of failure? Apathy? Or simply
            a lack of vision? Whatever the reason, mediocrity is a betrayal of
            our potential. It's the antithesis of what we, as creators, should
            strive for. We should be pushing boundaries, challenging
            conventions, and pouring our souls into our work. Anything less is
            an affront to the craft.</i
        >
    </p>
    <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10 mt-10">
        <span class="text-4xl">&#42;</span>
        <i
            >Rejecting mediocrity means embracing discomfort, demanding more
            from ourselves, and refusing to settle. It's about holding ourselves
            to a higher standard and recognizing that excellence is not a
            destination but a relentless pursuit. Let's not just make things
            that work; let's make things that inspire, that resonate, that stand
            the test of time. Because anything less is not just a disservice to
            ourselves, but to the world we aim to impact.</i
        >
    </p>

    <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10">
        <span class="text-4xl">&#42;</span>
        <i>
            <span class="font-bold underline underline-offset-8 decoration-wavy"
                >Open:</span
            > Embracing openness is more than a principle—it's a commitment. Transparency
            and collaboration aren't just buzzwords; they're the lifeblood of progress.
            In the spirit of open source, we stand by the belief that knowledge should
            be shared, communities should be nurtured, and every contribution fuels
            the collective growth of the development ecosystem. This is about tearing
            down walls, dissolving silos, and fostering an environment where ideas
            can cross-pollinate and flourish.</i
        >
    </p>

    <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed mb-10">
        <span class="text-4xl">&#42;</span>
        <i
            ><span
                class="font-bold underline underline-offset-8 decoration-wavy"
                >Void:</span
            > The void represents a canvas of boundless potential. Our projects are
            like the void—unfettered by predefined limits. This isn’t just a metaphor;
            it’s an ethos. We dive into the unknown, embracing the uncharted territory
            where true innovation lives. Here, we aren't just solving problems; we're
            redefining what's possible, constantly pushing the boundaries in pursuit
            of groundbreaking solutions.</i
        >
    </p>

    <h1 class="">&#42;&#47;</h1>
</PageLayout>
